abstract: Police arrest Gjergi Logu-Cupi, charging him with second-degree murder and other crimes in relation to deadly shooting in Queens, over double-parked car, that took life of Roberto Adames; case remained unsolved, despite number of witnesses, until recent tip.
lead_paragraph: After a tip in a long-dormant case, a 52-year-old man was charged with shooting two brothers, one of whom died, in a dispute over a double-parked car.

headline.main: Connecticut Man Is Charged in 2011 Murder in Queens Over Double-Parked Car
headline.print_headline: Arrest Is Made 4 Years After Fatal Shooting Over a Double-Parked Car in Queens
